Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check found that /etc/issue on this XCP-ng Dom0 (RHEL 7-based) system does not contain the required Standard Mandatory DoD Notice and Consent Banner or is missing key required phrases. Per RHEL 7 STIG requirement RHEL-07-010050, the operating system must display the DoD banner before granting command line access. Remediation: Update /etc/issue with the full Standard Mandatory DoD Notice and Consent Banner text as specified in the STIG check guidance. The banner must include all required elements: USG authorization notice, consent conditions, monitoring disclosure, data seizure rights, privacy limitations, and privileged communications exception. Finding: Open.
        

</COMMENTS>
