V-204405 - /etc/pam.d/passwd Must Use system-auth Substack
============================================================

Command: cat /etc/pam.d/passwd
Result:
#%PAM-1.0
auth       include	system-auth
account    include	system-auth
password   substack	system-auth
-password   optional	pam_gnome_keyring.so use_authtok
password   substack	postlogin

Command: grep -i substack /etc/pam.d/passwd
Result: password   substack	system-auth
password   substack	postlogin

PASS: /etc/pam.d/passwd uses system-auth substack for password changes.
</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/14/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_Dom0_RHEL7_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 1

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check verified that /etc/pam.d/passwd on this XCP-ng Dom0 (RHEL 7-based) system includes a substack reference to system-auth. This ensures that password changes go through the centralized PAM authentication stack defined in /etc/pam.d/system-auth, providing consistent password policy enforcement including complexity requirements (pam_pwquality), account lockout (pam_faillock), and password history (pam_pwhistory). Finding: Not a Finding.
        

</COMMENTS>
				<SEVERITY_OVERRIDE />
				<SEVERITY_JUSTIFICATION />
