V-204407 - Password Must Require Upper-case Character (ucredit)
============================================================

Command: grep ucredit /etc/security/pwquality.conf
Result: # ucredit = 1

FAIL: ucredit is not configured in /etc/security/pwquality.conf.
Remediation: Add to /etc/security/pwquality.conf:
  ucredit = -1
</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/14/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_Dom0_RHEL7_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check found that ucredit is either not configured or not set to a negative value in /etc/security/pwquality.conf on this XCP-ng Dom0 (RHEL 7-based) system. Without this setting, password changes may not require upper-case characters, reducing password complexity and making passwords more susceptible to brute-force attacks. Remediation: Add or modify the following line in /etc/security/pwquality.conf: ucredit = -1. This requires at least one upper-case character in new passwords. Finding: Open.
        

