V-204422 - Password Reuse Prohibited for 5 Generations (remember)
============================================================

Command: grep -i remember /etc/pam.d/system-auth
Result: 

Command: grep -i remember /etc/pam.d/password-auth
Result: 

system-auth remember value: 0
password-auth remember value: 0

FAIL: Password reuse must be prohibited for at least 5 generations.
Remediation: Add remember=5 to pam_unix.so or pam_pwhistory.so in both:
  /etc/pam.d/system-auth
  /etc/pam.d/password-auth
</FINDING_DETAILS>
