V-204424 - No Blank or Null Passwords Allowed
============================================================

Check 1: /etc/pam.d/system-auth
Command: grep -i nullok /etc/pam.d/system-auth
Result: auth        sufficient    pam_unix.so try_first_pass nullok
password    sufficient    pam_unix.so try_first_pass use_authtok nullok sha512 shadow

Check 2: /etc/pam.d/password-auth
Command: grep -i nullok /etc/pam.d/password-auth
Result: auth        sufficient    pam_unix.so try_first_pass nullok
password    sufficient    pam_unix.so try_first_pass use_authtok nullok sha512 shadow

FAIL: The nullok option allows accounts with blank passwords to authenticate.
Remediation: Remove all instances of 'nullok' from
/etc/pam.d/system-auth and /etc/pam.d/password-auth.
