V-204427 - Lock Accounts After 3 Failed Attempts (pam_faillock)
============================================================

Command: grep pam_faillock /etc/pam.d/password-auth
Result:


deny=0 (required: &lt;= 3)
fail_interval=0 (required: &gt;= 900)
unlock_time=0 (required: &gt;= 900 or 0=never)

FAIL: pam_faillock is not properly configured in password-auth.
Remediation: Configure pam_faillock.so with deny=3 fail_interval=900 unlock_time=900
</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/14/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_Dom0_RHEL7_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check found that pam_faillock.so is not properly configured in /etc/pam.d/password-auth. One or more required parameters (deny, fail_interval, unlock_time) are missing or set to non-compliant values. Remediation: Configure pam_faillock.so in /etc/pam.d/password-auth with deny=3, fail_interval=900, unlock_time=900 (or 0 for permanent lock). Finding: Open.
        

</COMMENTS>
				<SEVERITY_OVERRIDE />
				<SEVERITY_JUSTIFICATION />
