V-204447 - Repository GPG Signature Verification
============================================================

Command: grep -i gpgcheck /etc/yum.conf
Result: gpgcheck=1

PASS: yum is configured to verify GPG signatures (gpgcheck=1).
</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/14/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_Dom0_RHEL7_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 1

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check verified that yum on this XCP-ng Dom0 (RHEL 7-based) system is configured to verify GPG signatures for repository packages. The scan confirmed that gpgcheck=1 is set in /etc/yum.conf. This ensures that all packages installed from repositories have been digitally signed by a trusted Certificate Authority, preventing installation of tampered or unauthorized software. This meets RHEL 7 STIG requirement RHEL-07-020050 for repository package signature verification. XCP-ng repositories use GPG-signed packages to maintain supply chain integrity. Finding: Not a Finding.
        

</COMMENTS>
				<SEVERITY_OVERRIDE />
				<SEVERITY_JUSTIFICATION />
			</VULN>
