V-204448 - Local Package GPG Signature Verification
============================================================

Command: grep -i localpkg_gpgcheck /etc/yum.conf
Result: 

FAIL: localpkg_gpgcheck is not set to 1 in /etc/yum.conf.
Local packages may be installed without signature verification.
Remediation: Set localpkg_gpgcheck=1 in /etc/yum.conf
</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/14/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_Dom0_RHEL7_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check found that yum on this XCP-ng Dom0 (RHEL 7-based) system is not configured to verify GPG signatures for local packages. The localpkg_gpgcheck setting in /etc/yum.conf is not set to '1'. Per RHEL 7 STIG requirement RHEL-07-020060, the operating system must verify digital signatures before installing local packages. Without this check, manually-downloaded RPM files could be installed without signature verification. Remediation: (1) Edit /etc/yum.conf and set: localpkg_gpgcheck=1 in the [main] section. (2) Verify the change: grep localpkg_gpgcheck /etc/yum.conf. The system administrator must enable local package signature verification.
        

</COMMENTS>
				<SEVERITY_OVERRIDE />
				<SEVERITY_JUSTIFICATION />
			</VULN>
