				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/14/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_Dom0_RHEL7_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 1

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated STIG check verified whether the autofs (automount) service is installed and active on the XCP-ng Dom0 system. The check ran "rpm -q autofs" to determine if the package is installed, and if present, "systemctl is-active autofs" to verify the service state. On this system, autofs is either not installed or the service is inactive/disabled, confirming the automounter is not running. XCP-ng Dom0 does not require autofs for normal hypervisor operations, and NFS mounts if needed should be configured statically in /etc/fstab. This satisfies the RHEL 7 STIG requirement to disable the file system automounter unless operationally required and documented with the ISSO.

