V-204452 - Remove Old Software After Updates
============================================================

Command: grep -i clean_requirements_on_remove /etc/yum.conf
Result: 

FAIL: clean_requirements_on_remove is not set to 1/True/yes in /etc/yum.conf.
Remediation: Set clean_requirements_on_remove=1 in /etc/yum.conf
</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/14/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_Dom0_RHEL7_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check found that yum on this XCP-ng Dom0 system is not configured to remove old software after updates. The clean_requirements_on_remove setting in /etc/yum.conf is not set to 1. Per RHEL 7 STIG requirement RHEL-07-020200, old package dependencies must be removed after updates. Remediation: Set clean_requirements_on_remove=1 in /etc/yum.conf. The system administrator must configure automatic cleanup of obsolete packages.
        

