V-204453 - SELinux Must Be Enabled
============================================================

Command: getenforce
Result: Disabled

FAIL: SELinux is not in Enforcing mode (current: Disabled).
Note: XCP-ng Dom0 typically runs with SELinux disabled. This is a known finding.
</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/14/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_Dom0_RHEL7_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated STIG check ran "getenforce" and found that SELinux is not in Enforcing mode on the XCP-ng Dom0 system. XCP-ng Dom0 typically ships with SELinux disabled or in Permissive mode, which is a known compliance gap for RHEL 7 STIG requirements. The STIG requires SELinux to be active and in Enforcing mode. To remediate, edit /etc/selinux/config and set SELINUX=enforcing, then reboot. WARNING: Enabling SELinux on XCP-ng Dom0 may impact hypervisor operations and requires thorough testing. The system administrator should consult Vates support before enabling SELinux in production. This finding requires organizational risk acceptance if SELinux cannot be enabled.

</COMMENTS>
