V-204455 - Ctrl-Alt-Delete Key Sequence Disabled (CLI)
============================================================

Command: systemctl status ctrl-alt-del.target
Result:
 reboot.target - Reboot
   Loaded: loaded (/usr/lib/systemd/system/reboot.target; disabled; vendor preset: disabled)
   Active: inactive (dead)
     Docs: man:systemd.special(7)

FAIL: ctrl-alt-del.target is not masked.
Remediation:
  systemctl disable ctrl-alt-del.target
  systemctl mask ctrl-alt-del.target
</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/14/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_Dom0_RHEL7_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check found that the Ctrl-Alt-Delete key sequence is not properly disabled on this XCP-ng Dom0 (RHEL 7-based) system. The ctrl-alt-del.target systemd unit is not masked, which means the key combination could trigger an unintended system reboot. Per RHEL 7 STIG requirement RHEL-07-020230, the Ctrl-Alt-Delete sequence must be disabled to prevent accidental or malicious reboots. On a hypervisor Dom0, an unintended reboot would shut down all running virtual machines. Remediation: (1) Disable the target: systemctl disable ctrl-alt-del.target. (2) Mask the target: systemctl mask ctrl-alt-del.target. (3) Verify: systemctl status ctrl-alt-del.target (should show 'masked'). The system administrator must apply this change immediately.
        

</COMMENTS>
