V-204458 - OS Must Be Vendor-Supported Release
============================================================

Command: cat /etc/redhat-release
Result: XCP-ng release 8.3.0 (xenenterprise)

FAIL: Unable to confirm vendor support for this OS release.
Verify XCP-ng version is actively supported by Vates.
</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/14/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_Dom0_RHEL7_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check could not confirm that this XCP-ng Dom0 system is running a vendor-supported release. Per RHEL 7 STIG requirement RHEL-07-020250, the operating system must be a vendor-supported release to ensure security patches and updates are available. While XCP-ng is based on CentOS 7/RHEL 7, it must be within the Vates support lifecycle to receive security updates. Remediation: (1) Verify the XCP-ng version: cat /etc/xcp-ng-release. (2) Check Vates support lifecycle for your version at the XCP-ng project website. (3) If the version is end-of-life, plan migration to a supported version. (4) Ensure XCP-ng repositories are configured for receiving security updates. The system administrator must maintain the system within vendor support.
        

</COMMENTS>
