Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated STIG check found files or directories without a valid owner on the XCP-ng Dom0 system using "find / -maxdepth 5 -nouser". Unowned files may indicate deleted user accounts or improper file management, and they represent a security risk as they cannot be properly attributed for auditing purposes. To remediate, assign a valid owner to each unowned file using "chown &lt;user&gt; &lt;file&gt;". If the files are no longer needed, remove them. The system administrator should investigate why files lack ownership and ensure user account removal procedures include file ownership transfer.

</COMMENTS>
