V-204466 - Local Users Assigned Home Directory on Creation
============================================================

Command: grep -i ^CREATE_HOME /etc/login.defs
Result: CREATE_HOME	yes

PASS: CREATE_HOME is set to yes.
</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/14/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_Dom0_RHEL7_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 1

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated STIG check verified the CREATE_HOME parameter in /etc/login.defs on the XCP-ng Dom0 system. The check confirmed that CREATE_HOME is set to "yes", ensuring that when new local interactive user accounts are created using useradd, a home directory is automatically created for them. This prevents users from being created without a personal workspace and ensures proper file isolation between users. This satisfies the RHEL 7 STIG requirement.

</COMMENTS>
				<SEVERITY_OVERRIDE />
				<SEVERITY_JUSTIFICATION />
