Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_Dom0_RHEL7_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check found local initialization files that reference or execute programs from world-writable directories. This violates the STIG requirement because world-writable directories could contain trojan programs placed by malicious users. When an init file adds a world-writable directory to PATH or directly executes a program from such a location, the user is at risk of running malicious code during login. To remediate, remove references to world-writable directories from PATH in all init files and ensure no init file executes programs from world-writable locations.

