The automated check examines whether SELinux is enforcing on the XCP-ng Dom0 system and verifies that device files in /dev have proper SELinux context labels. On a properly configured system with SELinux enforcing, all device files should have an appropriate SELinux type label (such as device_t or a more specific type). The check verifies SELinux mode via getenforce and then examines device files for missing or incorrect SELinux labels using ls -lZ in the /dev directory.

