The automated check found that /dev/shm is missing one or more required mount options (nodev, nosuid, noexec) on this XCP-ng Dom0 system. Per RHEL 7 STIG requirement RHEL-07-021024, /dev/shm must be mounted with all three options. Remediation: Add to /etc/fstab: 'tmpfs /dev/shm tmpfs defaults,nodev,nosuid,noexec 0 0' then remount: mount -o remount /dev/shm. The system administrator must ensure shared memory is mounted securely.
        

