				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/14/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_Dom0_RHEL7_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check found that the kdump service is active on the system. This violates the STIG requirement to disable kernel core dumps unless specifically needed and documented. Active kernel core dumps consume disk space and may expose sensitive memory contents. To remediate, disable the kdump service: systemctl disable kdump.service and systemctl stop kdump.service. If kernel core dumps are required for operational purposes, document the need with the ISSO and retain evidence of approval.

</COMMENTS>
