V-204497 - FIPS-Validated Cryptography
============================================================

Check 1: dracut-fips package
Command: rpm -q dracut-fips
Result: package dracut-fips is not installed

FAIL: dracut-fips package is not installed.
FIPS mode cannot be enabled without dracut-fips.

Note: XCP-ng Dom0 may not support FIPS mode due to custom kernel.
This is a known compliance gap requiring Vates/vendor resolution.
</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/14/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_Dom0_RHEL7_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check found that this XCP-ng Dom0 (RHEL 7-based) system does not fully implement FIPS-validated cryptography. The scan detected that either the dracut-fips package is not installed, the fips=1 kernel parameter is missing from the boot command line, or FIPS mode is not active at runtime. Per RHEL 7 STIG requirement RHEL-07-021350, the operating system must implement NIST FIPS-validated cryptography. Note: XCP-ng Dom0 may not support FIPS mode due to its custom Xen kernel. This is a known compliance gap requiring Vates vendor resolution. Remediation: (1) Install dracut-fips: yum install dracut-fips. (2) Add fips=1 to GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX in /etc/default/grub. (3) Regenerate GRUB config: grub2-mkconfig -o /boot/grub2/grub.cfg. (4) Rebuild initramfs: dracut -f. (5) Reboot. Contact Vates for XCP-ng FIPS compatibility guidance.
        

</COMMENTS>
				<SEVERITY_OVERRIDE />
				<SEVERITY_JUSTIFICATION />
