V-204501 - Boot Loader on Removable Media
============================================================

grub.cfg locations found:
/boot/grub/grub.cfg
/etc/grub.cfg

Non-standard grub.cfg locations:
  /boot/grub/grub.cfg
  /etc/grub.cfg

RESULT: FAIL - Boot loader found on potential removable media
</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/14/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_Dom0_RHEL7_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check found grub.cfg boot loader configuration files in non-standard locations that may indicate removable media boot capability. This violates the STIG requirement because booting from removable media bypasses system security controls and could allow unauthorized operating system loading. To remediate, remove alternate boot loader configurations from removable media paths. If booting from removable media is operationally required, document the configuration with ISSO approval.

</COMMENTS>
