				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/14/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_Dom0_RHEL7_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 1

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check verified that the telnet-server package is not installed on this XCP-ng Dom0 (RHEL 7-based) system. The scan executed 'rpm -q telnet-server' and confirmed the package is not present. Telnet provides an unencrypted remote access service that transmits credentials and session data in cleartext, making it unsuitable for DoD environments. Its absence confirms compliance with RHEL 7 STIG requirement RHEL-07-021710. XCP-ng Dom0 uses SSH for all remote administration. Finding: Not a Finding.
        

</COMMENTS>
