				<STIG_DATA>
					<VULN_ATTRIBUTE>Check_Content</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
					<ATTRIBUTE_DATA>Verify the operating system produces audit records containing information to establish when (date and time) the events occurred.

Check to see if auditing is active by issuing the following command:

# systemctl is-active auditd.service
active

If the "auditd" status is not active, this is a finding.</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
				</STIG_DATA>
				<STIG_DATA>
					<VULN_ATTRIBUTE>Fix_Text</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
					<ATTRIBUTE_DATA>Configure the operating system to produce audit records containing information to establish when (date and time) the events occurred.

Enable the auditd service with the following command:

# systemctl start auditd.service</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
