V-204503 - Audit Service (auditd) Active
============================================================

auditd.service status: inactive

RESULT: FAIL - auditd service is not active
</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/14/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_Dom0_RHEL7_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check found that the auditd service is not active. This violates the STIG requirement for audit record generation. Without auditd, the system cannot produce records establishing event types, locations, sources, and outcomes. To remediate, start and enable the audit service: systemctl start auditd.service and systemctl enable auditd.service. Verify activation: systemctl is-active auditd.service should return active.

</COMMENTS>
				<SEVERITY_OVERRIDE />
