============================================================

auditctl -s output:
/usr/bin/timeout: failed to run command auditctl: No such file or directory

RESULT: FAIL - Unable to determine audit failure mode
</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/14/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_Dom0_RHEL7_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check found that the audit failure mode is not set to an acceptable value (1 or 2). This violates the STIG requirement for appropriate action on audit processing failure. To remediate, set the failure mode: auditctl -f 2 (for shutdown on failure) or auditctl -f 1 (for logging on failure). Make persistent by adding -f 2 to /etc/audit/rules.d/audit.rules. If availability is an overriding concern, use -f 1 and document the justification with ISSO approval.

</COMMENTS>
