The automated check examines /etc/audisp/audisp-remote.conf for the enable_krb5 setting on the XCP-ng Dom0 system. Kerberos 5 encryption must be enabled (enable_krb5=yes) to protect audit records during transfer to the remote audit server. Without encryption, audit records could be intercepted or modified in transit, compromising the integrity of the audit trail.

