					<ATTRIBUTE_DATA>Verify the operating system generates audit records when successful/unsuccessful attempts to use the "chcon" command occur.

Check the file system rule in "/etc/audit/audit.rules" with the following command:

$ sudo grep -w "/usr/bin/chcon" /etc/audit/audit.rules

-a always,exit -F path=/usr/bin/chcon -F perm=x -F auid&gt;=1000 -F auid!=unset -k privileged-priv_change

If the command does not return any output, this is a finding.</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
