V-204576 - Limit Concurrent Sessions to 10
============================================================

Command: grep -r maxlogins /etc/security/limits.conf /etc/security/limits.d/
Result: /etc/security/limits.conf:#        - maxlogins - max number of logins for this user
/etc/security/limits.conf:#@student        -       maxlogins       4

FAIL: maxlogins is not configured.
Remediation: Add '* hard maxlogins 10' to /etc/security/limits.conf
</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/14/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_Dom0_RHEL7_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check found that concurrent session limits are not properly configured on this XCP-ng Dom0 system. The 'maxlogins' setting is either missing or exceeds 10. Per RHEL 7 STIG requirement RHEL-07-040000, concurrent sessions must be limited to 10. Remediation: Add '* hard maxlogins 10' to /etc/security/limits.conf. The system administrator must configure session limits.
        

</COMMENTS>
