V-204594 - SSH Daemon Must Use Only SSHv2 Protocol
============================================================

OS Release: XCP-ng release 8.3.0 (xenenterprise)
Command: grep -i protocol /etc/ssh/sshd_config
Result: 

PASS: SSH daemon is configured to use only SSHv2 protocol.
</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/14/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_Dom0_RHEL7_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 1

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check verified that the SSH daemon on this XCP-ng Dom0 (RHEL 7-based) system is configured to use only the SSHv2 protocol. The scan checked /etc/ssh/sshd_config for the Protocol directive and confirmed that SSHv1 is not enabled. XCP-ng is based on CentOS 7.5+, which defaults to SSHv2 only. SSHv1 has known cryptographic weaknesses and must not be used. This meets RHEL 7 STIG requirement RHEL-07-040390. Finding: Not a Finding.
        

</COMMENTS>
				<SEVERITY_OVERRIDE />
				<SEVERITY_JUSTIFICATION />
