					<ATTRIBUTE_DATA>Note: For RHEL 7.4 and above, this requirement is not applicable.

Verify the SSH daemon performs compression after a user successfully authenticates.

Check that the SSH daemon performs compression after a user successfully authenticates with the following command:

     # grep -i compression /etc/ssh/sshd_config
     Compression delayed

If the "Compression" keyword is set to "yes", is missing, or the returned line is commented out, this is a finding.</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
				</STIG_DATA>
				<STIG_DATA>
					<VULN_ATTRIBUTE>Fix_Text</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
					<ATTRIBUTE_DATA>Uncomment the "Compression" keyword in "/etc/ssh/sshd_config" (this file may be named differently or be in a different location if using a version of SSH that is provided by a third-party vendor) on the system and set the value to "delayed" or "no":

     Compression no

The SSH service must be restarted for changes to take effect.</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
