V-204605 - Display Last Successful Logon Upon Login
============================================================

Command: grep pam_lastlog /etc/pam.d/postlogin
Result: session     [default=1]   pam_lastlog.so nowtmp showfailed
session     optional      pam_lastlog.so silent noupdate showfailed

FAIL: pam_lastlog is present but has the 'silent' option.
Remediation: Remove the 'silent' option from the pam_lastlog line.
</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/14/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_Dom0_RHEL7_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check found that the last logon information is not displayed upon login on this XCP-ng Dom0 system. Either pam_lastlog is missing from /etc/pam.d/postlogin or the 'silent' option suppresses the display. Per RHEL 7 STIG requirement RHEL-07-040530, last logon must be shown. Remediation: Add 'session required pam_lastlog.so showfailed' to /etc/pam.d/postlogin. Remove any 'silent' option. The system administrator must configure logon notification.
        

</COMMENTS>
