				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/14/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_Dom0_RHEL7_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 1

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check verified that the tftp-server package is not installed on this XCP-ng Dom0 (RHEL 7-based) system. The scan executed 'rpm -q tftp-server' and confirmed the package is not present. TFTP provides an unencrypted, unauthenticated file transfer service and must not be installed unless required for specific operational support (e.g., PXE boot). Its absence confirms compliance with RHEL 7 STIG requirement RHEL-07-040700. Finding: Not a Finding.
        

</COMMENTS>
				<SEVERITY_OVERRIDE />
				<SEVERITY_JUSTIFICATION />
