The automated check found no antivirus solution installed on this XCP-ng Dom0 (RHEL 7-based) system. The scan checked for ClamAV, McAfee, and CrowdStrike and found none. Per RHEL 7 STIG requirement RHEL-07-032000, all systems must have an antivirus program installed. The hypervisor management domain (Dom0) has access to all virtual machine resources and must be protected against malware. Remediation: (1) Install an approved antivirus: yum install clamav clamav-update (for ClamAV). (2) Configure automatic signature updates. (3) Enable on-access scanning if supported. (4) Schedule regular full system scans. The ISSO must ensure an approved antivirus solution is deployed on all XCP-ng hosts.
        

</COMMENTS>
				<SEVERITY_OVERRIDE />
				<SEVERITY_JUSTIFICATION />
			</VULN>
